('LOC_PEDIA_RELIGIONS_PAGE_SDG_POLYGAMY_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'Polygamy is the practice of marrying multiple spouses. When a man is married to more than one wife at a time, sociologists call this polygyny. When a woman is married to more than one husband at a time, it is called polyandry. If a marriage includes multiple husbands and wives, it can be called a group marriage.', 'en_US'),

