('LOC_PEDIA_RELIGIONS_PAGE_SDG_ITINERANT_MINISTERS_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'An itinerant preacher is a Christian evangelist who preaches the basic Christian redemption message while traveling around to different groups of people within a relatively short period of time. The movement is different from longer term church planting missions and discipleship.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Early 1st Century New Testament figures such as Paul of Tarsus were known for extensively traveling and preaching the Gospel to unreached peoples in the Middle East and Europe.', 'en_US'),

