('LOC_PEDIA_RELIGIONS_PAGE_SDG_SALT_OF_THE_EARTH_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'Jesus said to his followers, "You are the salt of the earth. But if the salt loses its saltiness, how can it be made salty again? It is no longer good for anything, except to be thrown out and trampled underfoot.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]"You are the light of the world. A town built on a hill cannot be hidden. Neither do people light a lamp and put it under a bowl. Instead they put it on its stand, and it gives light to everyone in the house. In the same way, let your light shine before others, that they may see your good deeds and glorify your Father in heaven.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]-Matthew 5:13-14', 'en_US'),

('LOC_SDG_JONAH', 'Jonah', 'en_US'),
('LOC_SDG_JONAH_DESCRIPTION', '+5[ICON_Faith]Faith on[ICON_RESOURCE_WHALES]Whales (also Orca, if playing with the Resourceful2 mod)[NEWLINE][in cities that follow this religion]', 'en_US'),
('LOC_PEDIA_RELIGIONS_PAGE_SDG_JONAH_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'Jonah is a prophet in the Old Testament whose story is told in the book of that name. Jonah is called by God to go to Nineveh (the capital of the Jews'' enemies, the Assyrians) to preach against them and tell them that their wickedness has come before God. Jonah chose to run away from God and board a ship going in the opposite direction. The Lord sent a storm that threatened to destroy the boat and when Jonah confessed to the sailors that he angered God, he asked to be thrown overboard for his sin. The sea calmed down and the Lord provided for a huge fish to swallow Jonah. Jonah was in the belly of the fish for 3 days and 3 nights before being vomited onto dry land and called again to preach against Nineveh. This time, Jonah obeyed, and, to his surprise, Nineveh repented and were spared from God''s wrath. Then Jonah sulks and the book ends.', 'en_US'),

