('LOC_PEDIA_RELIGIONS_PAGE_SDG_I_AM_DEATH_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', 'J. Robert Oppenheimer was the scientist chosen to head the Manhattan Project''s secret weapons laboratory tasked with creating the atomic bomb. Recalling his experience of the Trinity test, the first ever man-made nuclear explosion, he said:[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]"We knew the world would not be the same. A few people laughed, a few people cried. Most people were silent. I remembered the line from the Hindu scripture, the Bhagavad Gita; Vishnu is trying to persuade the Prince that he should do his duty and, to impress him, takes on his multi-armed form and says, ''Now I am become Death, the destroyer of worlds.''"', 'en_US'),



