('LOC_PEDIA_RELIGIONS_PAGE_SDG_XMAS_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1', '"Xmas" is an abbreviation for Christmas that dates back to the 15th century. However, in the 20th century the term took on a connotation of a "Christ-less" or secular Christmas that ritualizes the annual buying of gifts for friends and family over and above pious reverence for the birth of Jesus. Today Christmas is the peak selling season in many nations around the world and has a significant influence on the global economy.', 'en_US'),

